# Day 1 - Kali Linux Installation (Virtual Lab Setup)

## Objective

To set up a cybersecurity lab environment by installing Kali Linux using VirtualBox.

## Tools Required

* VirtualBox
  Download: https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

* Kali Linux (Prebuilt Virtual Machine)
  Download: https://www.kali.org/get-kali/#kali-virtual-machines

## Step 1: Install VirtualBox

* Download VirtualBox from the official website
* Run the installer and complete the installation
* Launch VirtualBox after installation

## Step 2: Download Kali Linux

* Go to the Kali Linux download page
* Download the "VirtualBox Image" (prebuilt file)
* Extract the downloaded file using WinRAR or 7-Zip

## Step 3: Import Kali Linux into VirtualBox

* Open VirtualBox
* Click on "Machine" → "Add"
* Select the extracted Kali Linux `.vbox` file
* Kali Linux will appear in the VirtualBox list

## Step 4: Start the Virtual Machine

* Select Kali Linux
* Click "Start"
* Wait for the system to boot

## Step 5: Login

Default credentials:

* Username: kali
* Password: kali

## Understanding Virtual Machines

A virtual machine is a software-based system that allows running an operating system inside another system. It is useful for safe testing and learning.

## Why Kali Linux?

Kali Linux is a penetration testing operating system used by security professionals for vulnerability testing and ethical hacking.

